attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPS32 ELF binary is identified as a variant of IoT malware, likely from the Mirai or Gafgyt families. The sample is packed, evidenced by the presence of the 'upx.sf.net' string and a custom unpacking stub in the entry point that utilizes sys_mmap and sys_mprotect to execute code in memory. Concrete indicators of malicious intent include hardcoded exploit paths for GPON routers ('/GponForm/diag_'), references to '/proc/self/exe' for self-persistence or evasion, and strings indicating HTTP-based C2 communication (POST requests with custom User-Agents).
